# Cat Scratch Fever
A roadmap-style card game built in Godot.

## Status
🚧 Mid Development 

##MVP: 
The Minimum Viable Product is a functional and playable strategy game in which the
user can play for a single "night" from start to finish. In this MVP, the player
draws a hand of song "cards" collected from a database of songs (initialized as
metadata) tagged by attributes including title, artist, genre, preference and
performs a set by choosing songs that best align with that audience. Each song
selection updates crowd energy, trust, and patience values according to risk 
calculations, energy fluctuations, and genre alignment. The session concludes after
either the player successfully performs 5 songs that align enough to achieve the 
minimum success requirement, or the user fails due to crowd energy, trust, or
patience sinking below the threshold of success. The MVP will demonstrate a 
complete gameplay loop, structured data uses, dynamic state updates, and win/lost
conditions.

## Quick Start
1. Open in Godot 4.x
2. Run the project

## Project Structure
- `/scenes` - scenes
- `/scripts -  scripts (song_database.gd)
- `/assets` - Art, audio, fonts

